Interface CurveExtrapolator

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Named

    public interface CurveExtrapolator
extends Named
    Interface for extrapolators which extrapolate beyond the ends of a curve.

      • bind

        BoundCurveExtrapolator bind(DoubleArray xValues,
                            DoubleArray yValues,
                            BoundCurveInterpolator interpolator)
        Binds this extrapolator to a curve.

        The bind process takes the definition of the extrapolator and combines it with the x-y values. This allows implementations to optimize extrapolation calculations.

        This method is intended to be called from within CurveInterpolator.bind(DoubleArray, DoubleArray, CurveExtrapolator, CurveExtrapolator). Callers should ensure that the interpolator instance passed in fully constructed. For example, it is incorrect to call this method from a BoundCurveInterpolator constructor.

        Parameters:
        xValues - the x-values of the curve, must be sorted from low to high
        yValues - the y-values of the curve
        interpolator - the interpolator
        Returns:
        the bound extrapolator
